Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_noise_propagation(25.10)                report_noise_propagation(25.10)

Name
       report_noise_propagation  - Prints text-based noise propagation reports
       that show glitch-source tracing for all the user-specified or  all-vio-
       lating receiver pins

Syntax
       report_noise_propagation

       [-help]

       [-level {VL | VH | worst | all}]

       [-max_paths <integer>]

       [-max_slack <float>]

       [-nets <string>]

       [-nworst <integer>]

       [-pins <string>]

       [-source_depth <integer>]

       [-views <string>]

       [ [ > | >> ] ]

       Prints  text-based  noise  propagation  reports that show glitch-source
       tracing for all the user-specified or all-violating receiver pins.  The
       report  allows  you  to  view full paths showing the glitch propagating
       from the source to the violating receiver pin.  This  helps  to  easily
       identify and fix glitch violations.

       Note: You need to set setSIMode -enable_glitch_report parameter to true
       to enable glitch reporting.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  out the command usage. For a detailed description of the
              command and all of its parameters, use the man command: man  re-
              port_noise_propagation

       -level {VL | VH | worst | all}
              Reports paths for specified glitch level. You can specify one of
              these options - VL, VH, worst, or all.

       -max_paths <integer>
              Reports the specified number of paths.

       -max_slack <float>
              Reports  paths  with  glitch  slack  equal to or lesser than the
              specified value.

       -nets <string>
              Reports paths with endpoint being all the input  pins  connected
              to the specified net.

       -nworst <integer>
              Specifies  the  maximum number of sources per endpoint for which
              paths need to be reported.

       -pins <string>
              Reports the paths for the specified endpoint pins.

       -source_depth <integer>
              Specifies the maximum number of sources  to  be  traced  in  any
              given branch in the fanin cone of violation.

       -views <string>
              Reports the paths for the specified view.

       > <filename>
              Redirects output to the specified file.

       >> <filename>
              Appends output to the specified output file.

